ontent%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ioana%20Marinescu%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691b1220abd5e944effad717%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIoana%20Marinescu%20suggested%20that%20we%20may%20already%20be%20approaching%20the%20point%20where%20AI%20begins%20to%20suppress%20wages.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ioana%20Marinescu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPenn%20professor%20Ioana%20Marinescu%20says%20AI%20may%20already%20be%20nearing%20the%20peak%20of%20its%20wage%20boost.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20Brookings%20model%20shows%20pay%20could%20fall%20once%20roughly%20a%20third%20of%20cognitive%20tasks%20are%20automated.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEarly%20signs%20include%20slowing%20wage%20growth%20and%20fewer%20workers%20in%20intelligence-sector%20jobs%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20AI%20can%20make%20workers%20more%20productive%20%E2%80%94%20helping%20them%20do%20more%2C%20faster%20%E2%80%94%20which%20tends%20to%20lift%20wages%20before%20automation%20starts%20to%20replace%20some%20of%20those%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepseek-researcher-chen-deli-china-jobs-ai-risk-tech-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBut%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20already%20be%20pushing%20wages%20toward%20their%20peak%2C%20said%20Ioana%20Marinescu%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20Penn's%20School%20of%20Social%20Policy%20%26amp%3B%20Practice%20and%20coauthor%20of%20a%20new%20Brookings%20Institution%20paper%20on%20%26quot%3Bintelligence%20saturation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20over%2014%25%20automation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20citing%20her%20research.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20closer%20to%20a%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-threatens-skills-with-mad-max-economy-warns-top-economist-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edecline%20in%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20no%20automation.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-on-wages-boom-bust-academic-analysis-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrookings%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20as%20soon%20as%20roughly%2037%25%20of%20cognitive%20or%20%26quot%3Bintelligence%26quot%3B%20tasks%20are%20automated%2C%20wage%20growth%20could%20start%20to%20reverse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20when%20the%20decline%20happens%20exactly%20depends%20on%20parameters%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd078b27-2c4c-44d6-a6ab-b8d81c16bb7d%5C%22%3EThe%20warning%20signs%20to%20watch%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20signs%20that%20we're%20nearing%20that%20peak%20will%20be%20slowing%20wage%20growth%20and%20a%20shift%20in%20employment%20away%20from%20intelligence-heavy%20jobs%20toward%20physical%20ones%2C%20Marinescu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20economy%20has%20already%20automated%20more%20than%2014%25%20of%20%26quot%3Bintelligence%26quot%3B%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20a%20share%20that's%20been%20steadily%20rising%20since%20the%201980s.%20She%20based%20that%20estimate%20on%20research%20showing%20that%20the%20share%20of%20routine%20cognitive%20jobs%20fell%20from%2049%25%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20and%201980s%20to%2035%25%20in%202018%20%E2%80%94%20a%2014-point%20drop%20she%20interprets%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20automation%20in%20intelligence-based%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20places%20us%20on%20the%20upward%20slope%20of%20what%20she%20and%20coauthor%20Konrad%20Kording%20call%20the%20AI%20pay%20curve%3A%20wages%20rise%20as%20workers%20use%20smarter%20tools%2C%20then%20flatten%2C%20and%20eventually%20decline%20as%20machines%20take%20over%20more%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20wages%20to%20ever%20decline%20due%20to%20automation%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20see%20a%20decrease%20in%20the%20share%20of%20workers%20in%20intelligence%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20would%20happen%2C%20for%20example%2C%20if%20job%20losses%20in%20tech%20are%20not%20compensated%20by%20job%20gains%20in%20other%20intelligence%20jobs%2C%20and%20if%20physical%20jobs%20stay%20steady.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20shift%20takes%20hold%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20if%20software%20developers%2C%20translators%2C%20or%20marketing%20writers%20are%20replaced%20by%20AI%20without%20new%20high-value%20roles%20emerging%20%E2%80%94%20the%20overall%20share%20of%20intelligence-sector%20employment%20could%20decline%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20a%20wage%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20men%20talk%20in%20a%20brick-walled%20office.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6903831d0be9845f2dc56511%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWages%20rise%20as%20workers%20use%20smarter%20tools%2C%20then%20flatten%2C%20professors%20say.%3Cp%3EMelia%20Russell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22035f5a47-aaed-4881-83a2-b68d5aeabefe%5C%22%3EWhich%20jobs%20could%20go%20first%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20fast%20the%20shift%20could%20happen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20model%20assumes%20automation%20starts%20with%20the%20easiest%20intelligence%20tasks%20to%20replace%2C%20Marinescu%20said%20%E2%80%94%20jobs%20where%20AI%20can%20quickly%20outperform%20humans%20in%20pattern%20recognition%2C%20translation%2C%20or%20basic%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20these%20jobs%20to%20decline%20first%2C%20for%20example%2C%20translators%20or%20basic%20marketing%20copywriting%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20are%20not%20replaced%20by%20other%20intelligence%20jobs%2C%20the%20share%20of%20jobs%20in%20intelligence%20will%20tend%20to%20decrease%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20wage%20declines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20quickly%20that%20shift%20happens%20depends%20on%20how%20closely%20the%20physical%20and%20intelligence%20sides%20of%20the%20economy%20are%20linked.%20When%20they%20become%20more%20interchangeable%2C%20wage%20losses%20accelerate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarinescu%20said%20pay%20tends%20to%20decline%20faster%20when%20AI%20can%20easily%20replace%20more%20types%20of%20human%20work%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20intelligence%20and%20physical%20sectors%20become%20more%20substitutable%2C%20workers%20who%20huddle%20in%20the%20physical%20sector%20benefit%20less%20from%20further%20automation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20the%20same%20is%20true%20within%20the%20intelligence%20sector%20itself%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20intelligence%20tasks%20become%20less%20substitutable%20with%20each%20other%2C%20wages%20grow%20for%20longer%2C%20but%20decline%20faster%20once%20they%20start%20to%20decline.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bd789c4-aaec-43d6-8546-499392eddacb%5C%22%3EWhat%20she's%20watching%20next%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarinescu%20said%20the%20single%20most%20important%20metric%20to%20track%20is%20the%20share%20of%20workers%20in%20physical%20versus%20intelligence-sector%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20in%20other%20words%2C%20whether%20humans%20are%20moving%20toward%20or%20away%20from%20the%20kinds%20of%20work%20AI%20can%20easily%20replace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20balance%20starts%20to%20shift%20%E2%80%94%20with%20more%20people%20leaving%20desk-based%20cognitive%20jobs%20for%20embodied%2C%20slower-growing%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20the%20AI%20pay%20curve%20may%20already%20be%20nearing%20its%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-pay-boost-could-soon-hit-peak-research-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763389078000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691b1220abd5e944effad717%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-pay-boost-could