and%20APAC%20businesses.%20There%20is%20no%20key-man%20clause%20for%20investors%20in%20the%20firm%2C%20meaning%20backers%20cannot%20pull%20their%20capital%20when%20Englander%20retires%20or%20leaves%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sign%20limited%20partners%20are%20investing%20in%20the%20firm%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%20not%20Englander.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennium%20is%20much%20larger%20than%20just%20Englander%2C%20and%20has%20been%20for%20some%20time.%20But%20the%20sale%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennium-sells-minority-stake-investors-14-billion-valuation-izzy-englander-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%2015%25%20stake%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20start%20of%20November%2C%20which%20valued%20the%20manager%20at%20%2414%20billion%2C%20is%20still%20a%20milestone%20for%20the%2036-year-old%20fund.%20Even%20in%20an%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-hedge-funds-became-more-institutional-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20has%20matured%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20it%20remains%20rare%20for%20hedge-fund%20founders%20to%20sell%20a%20part%20of%20their%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELongtime%20investors%20in%20the%20firm's%20fund%20now%20own%20a%20part%20of%20the%20business.%20Private%20banks%20such%20as%20Goldman%20Sachs%20and%20UBS%20pitched%20wealthy%20individuals%20on%20a%20chance%20to%20snag%20a%20slice%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20hedge%20funds%20in%20history.%20Senior%20executives%20were%20given%20a%20chance%20to%20buy%20into%20the%20partnership%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20firm's%20history%2C%20a%20person%20close%20to%20the%20manager%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20question%20is%20what%20comes%20next%20for%20the%20hedge%20fund%20industry's%20biggest%20employer.%20How%20big%20can%20the%20firm%20get%3F%20What%20asset%20classes%20and%20geographies%20will%20it%20expand%20into%20next%3F%20And%20who%20will%20take%20over%20for%20Englander%20when%20he%20calls%20it%20quits%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22051d3365-83ff-4ced-80f7-fc189a74bb3b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%24120%20billion%20on%20the%20horizon%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMillennium%20has%20quadrupled%20its%20assets%20in%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20but%20unlike%20peers%20such%20as%20Citadel%2C%20Point72%2C%20and%20D.E.%20Shaw%2C%20which%20have%20returned%20money%20to%20investors%20recently%2C%20the%20New%20York-based%20firm%20has%20continued%20to%20fundraise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20firm%20raised%20%2410%20billion%20in%20a%20private%20equity-style%20drawdown%20fund%2C%20which%20would%20only%20call%20on%20investor%20capital%20if%20it%20found%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20pitch%20to%20a%20group%20of%20wealthy%20clients%20included%20a%20chart%20projecting%20the%20firm's%20growth%20to%20%24120%20billion%20in%20assets%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20along%20with%20the%20subsequent%20revenue%20the%20firm%20would%20generate%20as%20it%20expanded%2C%20according%20to%20a%20private%20banker%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20because%20they%20aren't%20authorized%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20media.%20(Millennium's%20own%20marketing%20presentation%20to%20private%20wealth%20platforms%20and%20longtime%20LPs%20did%20not%20include%20any%20fundraising%20goal).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%2C%20which%20states%20on%20its%20website%20that%20it%20has%20more%20than%20330%20investing%20teams%20and%206%2C400%20people%20total%2C%20has%20been%20able%20to%20lock%20in%20capital%20for%20longer%20and%20longer%20durations.%20A%20five-year%20lockup%20is%20now%20typical%20for%20new%20cash%20coming%20into%20Millennium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20long-term%20capital%20gives%20the%20firm%20the%20ability%20to%20build%20into%20new%20areas%20that%20might%20not%20generate%20returns%20right%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e09eb33e-ae5e-431c-a6dc-ab42bba032d3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrivate%20markets%2C%20offices%20abroad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20place%20the%20firm%20is%20intent%20on%20expanding%20into%20is%20the%20lucrative%20private%20markets.%20Bloomberg%20reported%20last%20month%20that%20the%20firm%20expects%20to%20raise%20up%20to%20%245%20billion%20in%20its%20first%20fund%20that%20will%20focus%20on%20investments%20such%20as%20real%20estate%20and%20asset-backed%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20assets%20have%20swelled%20across%20the%20multistrategy%20sector%2C%20managers%20like%20Millennium%20have%20had%20to%20get%20creative%20about%20where%20to%20put%20their%20growing%20pile%20of%20assets.%20Longtime%20focuses%20like%20relative%20value%20strategies%2C%20long-short%20equity%2C%20and%20quantitative%20bets%20will%20still%20be%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20firm%2C%20but%20as%20those%20areas%20become%20more%20crowded%2C%20the%20firm%20has%20branched%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20split%20its%20fixed%20income%20and%20commodities%20unit%20into%20separate%20units%20in%20late%202023%2C%20as%20it%20has%20sought%20to%20become%20a%20larger%20player%20in%20the%20commodities%20space.%20While%20the%20firm%20has%20yet%20to%20match%20the%20profits%20generated%20in%20that%20space%20by%20rival%20Citadel%2C%20it's%20an%20area%20where%20Millennium%20plans%20to%20keep%20adding%20talent%20and%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20also%20now%20has%20more%20than%20140%20offices%20globally%2C%20with%20a%20majority%20of%20these%20locations%20housing%20investment%20staff.%20Millennium's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdubai-financial-services-expat-talent-hub-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMiddle%20East%20buildout%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20well-known%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20biggest%20Western%20player%20in%20Dubai%20by%20head%20count%2C%20with%20close%20to%20150%20people%20and%20space%20for%20100%20more%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20are%20also%20adding%20teams%20across%20Europe%20and%20Asia%20to%20continue%20to%20diversify.%20The%20firm%20just%20poached%20Schonfeld's%20head%20of%20EMEA%20fundamental%20equity%20business%20development%2C%20Sameer%20Buch%2C%20to%20join%20its%20team%20of%20internal%20recruiters%2C%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20move%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Millennium%20has%20been%2C%20by%20far%2C%20the%20most%20prominent%20backer%20of%20externally%20run%20funds%20among%20its%20multistrategy%20cohorts%2C%20funding%20dozens%20of%20separately%20managed%20accounts%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20increased%20attention%20to%20money%20managers%20outside%20the%20firm's%20walls%2C%20Millennium's%20hiring%20of%20internal%20talent%20is%20not%20slowing.%20As%20Business%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-fund-pay-poaching-relocation-mercenaries-buy-loyalty-millennium-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20hired%20about%20160%20portfolio%20managers%20in%202024%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20three%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4a3093c-9a18-4c81-8e04-75816b3ec078%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20will%20fill%20Izzy's%20shoes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEnglander%2C%20by%20all%20accounts%2C%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20go%20anywhere%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%2077-year-old%20billionaire%20has%20built%20up%20his%20bench%20with%20plenty%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-alumni-being-hired-by-top-hedge-funds-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eformer%20Goldman%20Sachs%20executives%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20he's%20ready%20to%20step%20down.%20All%20four%20members%20of%20his%20office%20of%20the%20CIO%20%E2%80%94%20Justin%20Gmelich%2C%20Scott%20Rofey%2C%20Paul%20Russo%2C%20and%20Jeff%20Verschleiser%20%E2%80%94%20were%20partners%20at%20the%20revered%20investment%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnglander's%20right-hand%20man%2C%20former%20Barclays%20and%20Lehman%20Brothers%20executive%20Ajay%20Nagpal%2C%20added%20President%20to%20his%20